comments: She has no clue what shes teaching she reads everything from power points..would NEVER TAKE HER AGAIN!!

If you have any love for the English language avoid this woman. There\'s an attendance policy but since she posts everything in class online there\'s no point in going, especially since the class is so boring you\'ll probably fall asleep anyway.

Class is very boring. But the homework and tests/quizzes are easy. She has her powerpoints on Angel so that you can study from those. Most difficult thing about this class is finding the will power to go. Good professor, just not the most exciting.

There is absolutely no reason to not do well in this class. Lecture notes were posted online, homework assignments covered relevant material, and she devoted large amounts of class time to reviewing homework assignments. It is true that her lectures can get dull, mainly because she spends so much time reviewing since so many students are apathetic.

class started easily enough, moving at fast pace but simple concepts easy to follow, but as the concepts got harder, she did not slow down,hard to stay awake in that class. but keeps students up to date on material by posting all lectures online. she wants everyone to do well but unfortunately not the most enthusiastic teacher.

She was very boring and read exactly off her power points. Her tests were very hard. She asked every five minutes if anyone had any questions, but wasn\'t very helpful. Almost everyone didn\'t have a clue what was going on, including me!

terrible, hard to understand, doesn\'t care about the students at all. in 50 minutes she said okay 111 times. she knows what she is talking about, just doesn\'t have a clue in the world as to how to teach.

Horrible teacher!!!! Not helpful at all, runs through things like we\'re all economists...and it\'s a 100 level course!!! Hard to understand because she talks too soft. Don\'t take her class unless absolutley needed!!
